  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "=General= A fine little area close to town. 5–10 boulders of a good height and with good rock quality. Fairly well developed, but there are a few more boulders around the edges. =Directions= Take Enköpingsvägen from Uppsala. At Skärfälten, turn left towards Hammarskog. After a couple of kilometres, park on the right, just before another sign for Hammarskog pointing right. Continue along the road, then head up left on a small gravel track, passing a low boulder in the field. The first larger boulder, bomstenen, is on the left just beyond the edge of the woods. A guide is available here: Media:Lilla_Bärsta.pdf =Problems=",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:lilla-barsta-bimbo"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {},
      "routes": {
        "lilla-barsta-bimbo-problem-1": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Magnificent line on a split boulder, with a three-metre hand-jam roof. Sit start as far in as possible, then climb out, over the lip and up.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:lilla-barsta-bimbo"
            ]
          }
        },
        "lilla-barsta-bimbo-problem-2": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Standing start to Klassklyftan, taking the vertical section of the crack.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:lilla-barsta-bimbo"
            ]
          }
        },
        "lilla-barsta-bimbo-problem-3": {
          "description": {
            "text": "On the first boulder, on the left-hand side of the road after the edge of the woods. The right-hand variant on the arete-like feature at the back.",
